Text.Value: No! I mean, I'm just - I quit. Nothing wrong with quitting a job.
They're better off without me. I'm scared. All I want is to go home.
When that army comes, I'll be ready. I promise.
You haven't heard? An army is coming. They're saying it's unstoppable.
I won't tell anyone. For the right price.
But I have to get away. There's an army coming, trying to kill us all!
How about I do it? Guards - wake up!
Wh - oh. What do you - what are you doing in here?
Go ahead. I'll tell them you're funding a ferry ticket with their stolen belongings.
I just wanted to be safe. I'm not a coward. I'm not.
Who do you think you are? Eh? You can't just - just accuse someone of - of being a thief!
Great idea. They can deal with you. Guards - wake up!
Will this get you home? ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Guards! You're being robbed!
My stash is up on the roof. Just take it. I'll find another way to get the gold.
Help! Someone's trying to kill me!
Gods, I hope they haven't put up the prices again.
I'm getting out of here, taking a ferry down the coast to get me home.
My wife said we have to stand and fight and - and I can't! I won't... I'm not made for this.
A thief's a thief. I don't care why you're doing it.
That ferry's my last chance out of here. Bakshi's got to have something that'll cover the rest of my fare.
Go on, get lost. You're not allowed in here.
You're not a Fist. Go on, get out, or - or I'll wake the others!

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Panicking and whispering, trying to avoid waking up his comrades
EditorData.NodeContext: realisation, turning to bluffing - he doesn't want to wake them

Text.Value: Stash? I - I don't know anything about that. I've been guarding this room the whole time.
'Course you are. I can't believe they expect me to die protecting lowlifes like you.
You've got no business being in here, so just clear off.
Sure. If you want me to tell them you were trying to steal their belongings.
I can't go yet, I'm waiting on your explanation. Why were you stealing?
Delve into the gnome's mind.
Attack.
You'll always have a warm welcome in Cloakwood, stranger. I promise.
You need to leave. Immediately. This is a restricted area. Fists only!
Why do you need to leave?
Hand over everything you stole, and I'll let you live long enough to run.
All right, all right. It's all hidden up on the roof.
I have to report this. You lot - wake up!
It's not fair to rob your colleagues, no matter how expensive the boat is.
I'm no thief! I - I was going to pay it back. Eventually. I just - I needed the gold.
Really? You'll just give it to me?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Player hands over the gold to the gnome (unseen)

Text.Value: What's got them so spooked?
I'm looking for the owner of that stash hidden on the roof. Know where I could find them?
How do you know about that? Did those crooks down the docks send you?
Are you blackmailing me?
You seem capable from where I'm standing.
Hand over the lockpick, you thieving little worm.
No, wait -
Those bloody crooks at the docks are charging triple, though. 'Danger money'. It's a joke!

EditorData.NodeContext: Pissed off that they're taking advantage

Text.Value: I'm guessing it was your stash I found on the roof, then?
Keep it down! Yes, it's my stash, but it's not - I wasn't - I just needed the gold.
I told them I'll get the money in time. Not my fault they're charging triple. 'Danger money' my arse.
Look - hidden up on the roof you'll find all the stuff I stole. You can have it.
Tell me what you're up to or I'll wake them myself.
Not by boat! It's the army marching towards us makes things dangerous.
Okay! But it's not - it isn't like that! I'm not a criminal! I just needed the gold.
Thank you. I'll never forget this. Never.
I've heard enough. Guards - I've spotted a thief!
What are you doing? Get out of my head!
They've got a point. These are dangerous times to be travelling.
Leave.
It's over, all right? Finished. Now get out. This is a restricted area.
Leave.
You'll be looked on as a coward for deserting your post.
I need gold, too. Give me yours, and this goes no further.
This area isn't open for the public. You need to leave.
You found my stash? Please - don't tell anyone. I just needed some quick gold!
I'm not a soldier. I only joined for the uniform and a warm bed.
Please - that won't be necessary. I - I just needed gold. That's all.
I'm not giving you anything.
Needed it for what?
So you're a deserter, then?
You already found my stash. That was all I had!

EditorData.NodeContext: Stash has been mentioned previously, he's outraged the player wants more still

Text.Value: *You notice the gnome slip a lockpick into his pocket.*
You shouldn't be in here. This barracks is private.
Get a grip. You're a soldier - act like one.

Synopsis:
The player walks into the barracks room and disturbs a Flaming Fist who seems to be breaking into a locked chest. During conversation, the player can challenge him, discover the location of his stash, or attempt to persuade him not to flee, and to protect the city.

The whole conversation should be in relatively low voice, as he doens't want to wake the others sleeping in the barracks.
